first.name: Gluttony
first.desc: When this Pokémon is holding a Berry that usually activates with 1/4 or less of its maximum HP, it is eaten at 1/2 or less of its maximum HP instead.
first.shortDesc: This Pokémon eats Berries at 1/2 max HP or less instead of their usual 1/4 max HP.

second.name: Hustle
second.desc: This Pokémon's Attack is multiplied by 1.5 and the accuracy of its physical attacks is multiplied by 0.8.
second.isFieldAbility: If you have a Pokémon with Hustle at the front of your party (even if fainted), there is a 50% chance that a Pokémon will be forced to the upper bound of their encounter level range.
second.shortDesc: This Pokémon's Attack is 1.5x and accuracy of its physical attacks is 0.8x.

hidden.name: Thick Fat
hidden.desc: If a Pokémon uses a Fire- or Ice-type attack against this Pokémon, that Pokémon's offensive stat is halved when calculating the damage to this Pokémon.
hidden.shortDesc: Fire-/Ice-type moves against this Pokémon deal damage with a halved offensive stat.

move.desc: Deals damage to the last opposing Pokémon to hit the user with a physical attack this turn equal to twice the HP lost by the user from that attack. If the user did not lose HP from the attack, this move deals 1 HP of damage instead. If that opposing Pokémon's position is no longer in use and there is another opposing Pokémon on the field, the damage is done to it instead. Only the last hit of a multi-hit attack is counted. Fails if the user was not hit by an opposing Pokémon's physical attack this turn.
move.name: Counter
move.shortDesc: If hit by physical attack, returns double damage.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to the user's current HP. If this move is successful, the user faints.
move.name: Final Gambit
move.shortDesc: Does damage equal to the user's HP. User faints.

move.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 35% chance to hit two or three times and a 15% chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times.
move.name: Fury Swipes
move.shortDesc: Hits 2-5 times in one turn.

move.desc: The user uses the move the target chose for use this turn against it, if possible, with its power multiplied by 1.5. The move must be a damaging move other than Beak Blast, Belch, Blazing Torque, Combat Torque, Comeuppance, Counter, Covet, Focus Punch, Magical Torque, Me First, Metal Burst, Mirror Coat, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Struggle, Thief, or Wicked Torque. Fails if the target moves before the user. Ignores the target's substitute for the purpose of copying the move.
move.name: Me First
move.shortDesc: Copies a foe at 1.5x power. User must be faster.

move.desc: Power doubles if the user was hit by the target this turn.
move.name: Revenge
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is damaged by the target.

move.desc: The power of this move is 20 if X is 33 to 48, 40 if X is 17 to 32, 80 if X is 10 to 16, 100 if X is 5 to 9, 150 if X is 2 to 4, and 200 if X is 0 or 1, where X is equal to (user's current HP * 48 / user's maximum HP), rounded down.
move.name: Reversal
move.shortDesc: More power the less HP the user has left.

move.desc: If another Pokémon uses certain non-damaging moves this turn, the user steals that move to use itself. If multiple Pokémon use one of those moves this turn, the applicable moves are all stolen by the first Pokémon in turn order that used this move this turn. This effect is ignored while the user is under the effect of Sky Drop.
move.name: Snatch
move.shortDesc: User steals certain support moves to use itself.

move.desc: Raises the user's Defense and Special Defense by 1 stage. The user's Stockpile count increases by 1. Fails if the user's Stockpile count is 3. The user's Stockpile count is reset to 0 when it is no longer active.
move.name: Stockpile
move.shortDesc: Raises user's Defense, Sp. Def by 1. Max 3 uses.

move.desc: The user restores its HP based on its Stockpile count. Restores 1/4 of its maximum HP if it's 1, 1/2 of its maximum HP if it's 2, both rounded half down, and all of its HP if it's 3. Fails if the user's Stockpile count is 0. The user's Defense and Special Defense decrease by as many stages as Stockpile had increased them, and the user's Stockpile count resets to 0.
move.name: Swallow
move.shortDesc: Heals the user based on uses of Stockpile.

move.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Z-Crystal, if neither is holding an item, if the user is trying to give or take a Mega Stone to or from the species that can Mega Evolve with it, or if the user is trying to give or take a Blue Orb, a Red Orb, a Griseous Orb, a Plate, a Drive, or a Memory to or from a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, or a Silvally, respectively. The target is immune to this move if it has the Sticky Hold Ability.
move.name: Switcheroo
move.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

move.desc: The user spends three turns locked into this move. This move targets an opponent at random on each turn. On the first of the three turns, all sleeping active Pokémon wake up. During the three turns, no active Pokémon can fall asleep by any means, and Pokémon switched in during the effect do not wake up. If the user is prevented from moving or the attack is not successful against the target during one of the turns, the effect ends.
move.name: Uproar
move.shortDesc: Lasts 3 turns. Active Pokémon cannot fall asleep.

move.desc: Causes the target to become infatuated, making it unable to attack 50% of the time. Fails if both the user and the target are the same gender, if either is genderless, or if the target is already infatuated. The effect ends when either the user or the target is no longer active. Pokémon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
move.name: Attract
move.shortDesc: A target of the opposite gender gets infatuated.

move.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target. If the weather is Snow, this move does not check accuracy.
move.name: Blizzard
move.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze foe(s). Can't miss in Snow.

move.desc: Lowers the target's Special Attack by 1 stage.
move.name: Confide
move.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Atk by 1.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Dark Pulse
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: Raises the user's evasiveness by 1 stage.
move.name: Double Team
move.shortDesc: Raises the user's evasiveness by 1.

move.desc: For 5 turns, the target's held item has no effect. An item's effect of causing forme changes is unaffected, but any other effects from such items are negated. During the effect, Fling and Natural Gift are prevented from being used by the target. Items thrown at the target with Fling will still activate for it. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will remain unable to use items.
move.name: Embargo
move.shortDesc: For 5 turns, the target's item has no effect.

move.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
move.name: Facade
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

move.desc: Power is equal to the greater of ((255 - user's Happiness) * 2/5), rounded down, or 1.
move.name: Frustration
move.shortDesc: Max 102 power at minimum Happiness.

move.desc: This move's power is 20 if the target weighs less than 10 kg, 40 if less than 25 kg, 60 if less than 50 kg, 80 if less than 100 kg, 100 if less than 200 kg, and 120 if greater than or equal to 200 kg.
move.name: Grass Knot
move.shortDesc: More power the heavier the target.

move.desc: This move's type depends on the user's individual values (IVs), and can be any type but Fairy and Normal.
move.name: Hidden Power
move.shortDesc: Varies in type based on the user's IVs.

move.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.
move.name: Ice Beam
move.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze the target.

move.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokémon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
move.name: Protect
move.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

move.desc: Causes the target to take its turn after all other Pokémon this turn, no matter the priority of its selected move. Fails if the target already moved this turn.
move.name: Quash
move.shortDesc: Forces the target to move last this turn.

move.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
move.name: Rain Dance
move.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

move.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
move.name: Rest
move.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

move.desc: Power is equal to the greater of (user's Happiness * 2/5), rounded down, or 1.
move.name: Return
move.shortDesc: Max 102 power at maximum Happiness.

move.desc: If there are other active Pokémon that chose this move for use this turn, those Pokémon take their turn immediately after the user, in Speed order, and this move's power is 120 for each other user.
move.name: Round
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if others used Round this turn.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Shadow Ball
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

move.desc: Has a higher chance for a critical hit.
move.name: Shadow Claw
move.shortDesc: High critical hit ratio.

move.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
move.name: Sleep Talk
move.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.
move.name: Sludge Bomb
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to poison the target.

move.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Special Attack by 1 stage.
move.name: Snarl
move.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Sp. Atk by 1.

move.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokémon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokémon. Sound-based moves and Pokémon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
move.name: Substitute
move.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

move.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
move.name: Sunny Day
move.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

move.desc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 stages and confuses it.
move.name: Swagger
move.shortDesc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 and confuses it.

move.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokémon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
move.name: Taunt
move.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

move.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokémon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
move.name: Thief
move.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

move.desc: Prevents the target from selecting the same move for use two turns in a row. This effect ends when the target is no longer active.
move.name: Torment
move.shortDesc: Target can't select the same move twice in a row.

move.desc: Badly poisons the target. If a Poison-type Pokémon uses this move, the target cannot avoid the attack, even if the target is in the middle of a two-turn move.
move.name: Toxic
move.shortDesc: Badly poisons the target. Poison types can't miss.

move.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
move.name: U-turn
move.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

move.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokémon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
move.name: Covet
move.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
move.name: Endeavor
move.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

move.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
move.name: Icy Wind
move.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Iron Tail
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

move.desc: This move fails unless the user knows this move and at least one other move, and has used all the other moves it knows at least once each since it became active or Transformed.
move.name: Last Resort
move.shortDesc: Fails unless each known move has been used.

move.desc: This move does not check accuracy.
move.name: Shock Wave
move.shortDesc: This move does not check accuracy.

move.desc: If another Pokémon uses certain non-damaging moves this turn, the user steals that move to use itself. If multiple Pokémon use one of those moves this turn, the applicable moves are all stolen by the first Pokémon in turn order that used this move this turn. This effect is ignored while the user is under the effect of Sky Drop.
move.name: Snatch
move.shortDesc: User steals certain support moves to use itself.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch. Fails if the user is not asleep.
move.name: Snore
move.shortDesc: User must be asleep. 30% chance to flinch target.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to half of its current HP, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
move.name: Super Fang
move.shortDesc: Does damage equal to 1/2 target's current HP.

move.desc: The user spends three turns locked into this move. This move targets an opponent at random on each turn. On the first of the three turns, all sleeping active Pokémon wake up. move.name: Uproar
move.shortDesc: Lasts 3 turns. Active Pokémon cannot fall asleep.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Zen Headbutt
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: Power doubles if the target has already taken damage this turn, other than direct damage from Belly Drum, confusion, Curse, or Pain Split.
move.name: Assurance
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if target was damaged this turn.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Bite
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Crunch
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

move.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
move.name: Double-Edge
move.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
move.name: Endeavor
move.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

move.desc: Raises the user's chance for a critical hit by 2 stages. Fails if the user already has the effect. Baton Pass can be used to transfer this effect to an ally.
move.name: Focus Energy
move.shortDesc: Raises the user's critical hit ratio by 2.

move.desc: Has a 10% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Hyper Fang
move.shortDesc: 10% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: If an opposing Pokémon switches out this turn, this move hits that Pokémon before it leaves the field, even if it was not the original target. If the user moves after an opponent using Flip Turn, Parting Shot, Teleport, U-turn, or Volt Switch, but not Baton Pass, it will hit that opponent before it leaves the field. Power doubles and no accuracy check is done if the user hits an opponent switching out, and the user's turn is over; if an opponent faints from this, the replacement Pokémon does not become active until the end of the turn.
move.name: Pursuit
move.shortDesc: If a foe is switching out, hits it at 2x power.

move.desc: No additional effect.
move.name: Quick Attack
move.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

move.desc: Fails if the target did not select a physical attack, special attack, or Me First for use this turn, or if the target moves before the user.
move.name: Sucker Punch
move.shortDesc: Usually goes first. Fails if target is not attacking.

move.name: Super Fang
move.shortDesc: Does damage equal to 1/2 target's current HP.

move.desc: No additional effect.
move.name: Tackle
move.shortDesc: No additional effect.

move.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Tail Whip
move.shortDesc: Lowers the foe(s) Defense by 1.

move.desc: Causes the target to take its turn after all other Pokémon this turn, no matter the priority of its selected move. Fails if the target already moved this turn.
move.name: Quash
move.shortDesc: Forces the target to move last this turn.

move.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
move.name: Rain Dance
move.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

move.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
move.name: Rest
move.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

move.desc: Power is equal to the greater of (user's Happiness * 2/5), rounded down, or 1.
move.name: Return
move.shortDesc: Max 102 power at maximum Happiness.

move.desc: If there are other active Pokémon that chose this move for use this turn, those Pokémon take their turn immediately after the user, in Speed order, and this move's power is 120 for each other user.
move.name: Round
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if others used Round this turn.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Shadow Ball
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

move.desc: Has a higher chance for a critical hit.
move.name: Shadow Claw
move.shortDesc: High critical hit ratio.

move.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
move.name: Sleep Talk
move.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.
move.name: Sludge Bomb
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to poison the target.

move.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Special Attack by 1 stage.
move.name: Snarl
move.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Sp. Atk by 1.

move.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokémon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokémon. Sound-based moves and Pokémon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
move.name: Substitute
move.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

move.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
move.name: Sunny Day
move.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

move.desc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 stages and confuses it.
move.name: Swagger
move.shortDesc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 and confuses it.

move.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokémon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
move.name: Taunt
move.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

move.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokémon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
move.name: Thief
move.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

move.desc: Prevents the target from selecting the same move for use two turns in a row. This effect ends when the target is no longer active.
move.name: Torment
move.shortDesc: Target can't select the same move twice in a row.

move.desc: Badly poisons the target. If a Poison-type Pokémon uses this move, the target cannot avoid the attack, even if the target is in the middle of a two-turn move.
move.name: Toxic
move.shortDesc: Badly poisons the target. Poison types can't miss.

move.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
move.name: U-turn
move.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

move.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokémon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
move.name: Covet
move.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
move.name: Endeavor
move.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

move.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
move.name: Icy Wind
move.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Iron Tail
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

move.desc: This move fails unless the user knows this move and at least one other move, and has used all the other moves it knows at least once each since it became active or Transformed.
move.name: Last Resort
move.shortDesc: Fails unless each known move has been used.

move.desc: This move does not check accuracy.
move.name: Shock Wave
move.shortDesc: This move does not check accuracy.

move.desc: If another Pokémon uses certain non-damaging moves this turn, the user steals that move to use itself. If multiple Pokémon use one of those moves this turn, the applicable moves are all stolen by the first Pokémon in turn order that used this move this turn. This effect is ignored while the user is under the effect of Sky Drop.
move.name: Snatch
move.shortDesc: User steals certain support moves to use itself.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch. Fails if the user is not asleep.
move.name: Snore
move.shortDesc: User must be asleep. 30% chance to flinch target.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to half of its current HP, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
move.name: Super Fang
move.shortDesc: Does damage equal to 1/2 target's current HP.

move.desc: The user spends three turns locked into this move. This move targets an opponent at random on each turn. On the first of the three turns, all sleeping active Pokémon wake up. During the three turns, no active Pokémon can fall asleep by any means, and Pokémon switched in during the effect do not wake up. If the user is prevented from moving or the attack is not successful against the target during one of the turns, the effect ends.
move.name: Uproar
move.shortDesc: Lasts 3 turns. Active Pokémon cannot fall asleep.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Zen Headbutt
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: Power doubles if the target has already taken damage this turn, other than direct damage from Belly Drum, confusion, Curse, or Pain Split.
move.name: Assurance
move.shortDesc: Power doubles if target was damaged this turn.

move.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Bite
move.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Crunch
move.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

move.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
move.name: Double-Edge
move.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
move.name: Endeavor
move.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

move.desc: Raises the user's chance for a critical hit by 2 stages. Fails if the user already has the effect. Baton Pass can be used to transfer this effect to an ally.
move.name: Focus Energy
move.shortDesc: Raises the user's critical hit ratio by 2.

move.desc: Has a 10% chance to make the target flinch.
move.name: Hyper Fang
move.shortDesc: 10% chance to make the target flinch.

move.desc: If an opposing Pokémon switches out this turn, this move hits that Pokémon before it leaves the field, even if it was not the original target. If the user moves after an opponent using Flip Turn, Parting Shot, Teleport, U-turn, or Volt Switch, but not Baton Pass, it will hit that opponent before it leaves the field. Power doubles and no accuracy check is done if the user hits an opponent switching out, and the user's turn is over; if an opponent faints from this, the replacement Pokémon does not become active until the end of the turn.
move.name: Pursuit
move.shortDesc: If a foe is switching out, hits it at 2x power.

move.desc: No additional effect.
move.name: Quick Attack
move.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

move.desc: Fails if the target did not select a physical attack, special attack, or Me First for use this turn, or if the target moves before the user.
move.name: Sucker Punch
move.shortDesc: Usually goes first. Fails if target is not attacking.

move.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to half of its current HP, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
move.name: Super Fang
move.shortDesc: Does damage equal to 1/2 target's current HP.

move.desc: No additional effect.
move.name: Tackle
move.shortDesc: No additional effect.

move.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 1 stage.
move.name: Tail Whip
move.shortDesc: Lowers the foe(s) Defense by 1.

flavorTexts.flavor: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.
